{"id":"1301.7543","submitter":"Sen Zhang","authors":"S. Iso, K. Yamamoto, S. Zhang","title":"On the Cancellation Mechanism of Radiation from the Unruh detector","comments":"20 pages, 1 figure","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1093/ptep/ptt040","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th gr-qc","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A uniformly accelerated detector (Unruh detector) in the Minkowski vacuum is\nexcited as if it is exposed to the thermal bath with temperature proportional\nto its acceleration. In the inertial frame, since both of an excitation and a\ndeexcitation of the detector are accompanied by emission of radiation into the\nMinkowski vacuum, one may suspect that the Unruh detector emits radiation like\nthe Larmor radiation from an accelerated charged particle. However, it is known\nthat the radiation is miraculously cancelled by a quantum interference effect.\nIn this paper, we investigate under what condition the radiation cancels out.\nWe first show that the cancellation occurs if the Green function satisfies a\nrelation similar to the Kubo-Martin-Schwinger (KMS) condition. We then study\ntwo examples, Unruh detectors in the 3+1 dimensional Minkowski spacetime and in\nthe de Sitter spacetime. In both cases, the relation holds only in a restricted\nregion of the spacetime, but the radiation is cancelled in the whole spacetime.\nHence the KMS-like relation is necessary but not sufficient for the\ncancellation to occur.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 31 Jan 2013 08:31:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-21"}
